{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in pollock, lemon juice and salt. Remove bowl from lid, stir then set aside.","Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic and sun-dried tomatoes in mixing bowl then chop <b>2 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add spinach, ½ tsp salt and ¼ tsp pepper then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Preheat oven to 200°C. Grease a deep baking dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm x 5 cm).","Place butter, flour, milk, ¾ tsp salt, ½ tsp pepper, nutmeg and basil in mixing bowl then cook <b>10 min\/80°C\/speed 4<b>.","Spread 3 Tbsp white sauce in prepared baking dish, line with 3 lasagne sheets, spread ⅓ spinach over pasta, then arrange ⅓ reserved pollock. Repeat twice, finishing with a final pasta layer and a topping of remaining sauce, reserved Parmesan and mozzarella. Bake for 30 minutes (200°C) until golden and bubbling.","Leave to rest for 5 minutes befor serving hot, cut in portions."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g pollock, sliced (1 cm)","2 Tbsp lemon juice","1 ¾ tsp fine sea salt","50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","2 garlic cloves","30 g sun-dried tomatoes in oil, drained","300 g chopped spinach, frozen, thawed, drained","¾ tsp ground black pepper","40 g butter, diced, plus extra for greasing","70 g plain flour","650 g milk","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","½ tsp dried basil","12 dried lasagne sheets","120 g mozzarella, sliced (5 mm)"]}],"id":"r144440","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-ykpHAeYRqNM\/XZVRnvZPiyI\/AAAAAAAAdQ0\/bSFfOn0Lb4INSsTniidq9jOxjIQctp0MwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_tCSbwlbee380LUmA.png","title":"Pollock and Spinach Lasagne","publishedAt":"2017-03-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"35.7 g","fat":"18 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"47.3 g","calories":"2066 kJ \/ 494 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, rectangular baking dish (approx. 30 cm x 20 cm x 5 cm), oven","basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","6 portions"]}